properties.INTERESTING: Dravian Starport-based cargo merchants Topatz Shipping were offering payment of 4,500 credits to transport one hundred tons of imitation gemstones to Bazaar

properties.NAME: Rial Kroon system
properties.INTERESTING: advanced vulture droids first seen here, fighting against Rodian Jedi Master Toluz Cheq and his Padawan, who were both killed in the battle

properties.NAME: Homana system
properties.INTERESTING: Homanans: mysterious shape-shifters who could change from Wookiee-size to Ewok-size, could mimic clothes, were slightly telepathic, numbered less than 1M by 25 ABY; explored between 3000 and 1000 BBY

properties.NAME: Corosia system
properties.INTERESTING: home to Corosian phoenix (bird renowned for beauty)

properties.NAME: Vesla system
properties.INTERESTING: system's star was siphoned by Darth Mekhis's Sun Razer superweapon until it was destroyed by Theron Shan

properties.NAME: Prolifera system
properties.INTERESTING: Proliferans: non-humanoid insectoids who resembled large red ants and were skilled diggers; shared name with Proliferan Empire, ruled by a monarch (Queen Yentuki during GCW)

properties.NAME: Tangrada
properties.INTERESTING: Tangrada-Nii (culture that later begat the Tagra-Tel culture) believed the Oridol star cluster was the face of their god; the Tagra-Tel sent starships into the cluster over a number of centuries and concluded it was alive after experiencing paranormal activity

properties.NAME: Kurluvion system
properties.INTERESTING: a Snivvian patron of Chalmun's Cantina approached Han with a shipment of holographic Hutt-smut to be delivered here, where it was extremely popular

properties.NAME: Guuko system
properties.INTERESTING: origin point of Guukosi (group) as well as Guuko Pure Light party (organization that once carried out genocide against Guukosi and used a winged circle as their symbol)

properties.NAME: Harrikos system
properties.NOTES: could add more info to WP

properties.INTERESTING: a short hyperspace jump from Jiruus; source of legends by the Tangrada-Nii and subsequent Tagra-Tel cultures); site of running battle between NR Nebulon-B frigate Hellion's Dare and the Imperial Quasar Fire-class cruiser-carrier Aerie (carrying two squadrons of the 204th Imperial Fighter wing, also known as Shadow Wing; the Hellion's Dare was destroyed here

properties.NAME: Marcellus Nebula
properties.INTERESTING: contained Marcellus system

properties.NAME: Lorardia system
properties.INTERESTING: during Cold War, survey team charting uninhabited terrestrial world in system recieved unusual readings caused by large deposits of maranium under the surface

properties.NAME: Flyntaria system
properties.INTERESTING: origin point of Flyntarian tabac stick

properties.NAME: Cedre system
properties.INTERESTING: system contained 6 stars; roughly 3 light-years from Dathomir

properties.NAME: Landor system
properties.INTERESTING: known to be pirate-infested c. 44 BBY

properties.NAME: Galltine

properties.NAME: Druulgotha system
properties.INTERESTING: Druulgothans: lizard-like

properties.NAME: Wrodi system
properties.INTERESTING: origin point of Wrodian carpets

properties.NAME: Thomquizzar system
properties.INTERESTING: location of dirtside Thomquizzar (Imperial) Naval Base, constructed before 0 BBY

properties.NAME: Crombach Nebula
properties.INTERESTING: Irmenu system was located in fringes of nebula; navigational hazard for centuries; bridged by Freia Kallea in 3705 BBY when she linked the Mandalorian Road to the Sprizen End Run as part of her blazing of the Hydian Way; site of Battle of Crombach Nebula during CW, where Wom-Nii Gnaden (Jedi Master) was killed

properties.NAME: Denarii Station
properties.INTERESTING: scientific observation post in Denarii Nebula; orignally used by astrophysicists for studying the nebula; fell into disuse centuries befoe 43 ABY, but still used by desperate as a hideout

properties.NAME: Denarii N.
properties.INTERESTING: remnant of double-star supernova destroyed by Naga Sadow during Great Hyperspace War of 5000 BBY

properties.NAME: Jovan system
properties.INTERESTING: uneventful system focused on agricultural activities, according to Sax Hastur (TIE Pilot); Empire was to send a task force to Jovan system right after Battle of Portocari

properties.NAME: Kravos system
properties.INTERESTING: dead system on the edge of Sith Empire space, filled with ionized gas, due to a partially dispersed accretion disk; orange-colored gas giant formed nearby; Zeerid Korr and Aryn Leneer traveled there while trying to get to Sith Empire-held Coruscant by using an electromagnetic clamp to latch onto a ship in an Imperial convoy

properties.NAME: Far Indosa system
properties.INTERESTING: many miners left Near Indosa for this system because it held more prospects for continued mining after millennia of mining drained Near Indosa of its mineral resources

properties.NAME: Ie-Tikkaht
properties.INTERESTING: (placeholder name given); ashen planet; by 4 ABY, spice-mining outpost of no more than a few thousand colonists; Imperial colonel Shakara Nuress traveled here aboard the ISD Pursuer and obliterated the colony from orbit to protect the location of the 204th Imperial Fighter Wing's nearby base on Pandem Nai; afterward, 4 other outposts in 3 nearby systems remained nearby to target

properties.NAME: Traptoforia system
properties.INTERESTING: home to Traptoforian razor-slugs

properties.NAME: Zona Miki system
properties.INTERESTING: by 1750 BBY, Dark underlord (new Sith leader) assailed the space stations along the Zona Miki route with his Black Knights; the Republic hired Mandalorian mercenaries who helped defeat him on Malrev IV

properties.NAME: Barison
properties.INTERESTING: waterworld which supplied fish, kelp, and seafood to worlds in the Back Reach; Barisoni: many renounced technology for religious reasons; Airen Cracken had to rescue his droid Vee Gee from Barisoni pirates using a restraining bolt deactivator

properties.NAME: Vallusk Cluster
properties.INTERESTING: no habitable worlds; common location for starships to exit hyperspace and recalibrate navicomputers for a trip to Arkuda; Ackbar engaged four ISDs here as a distraction so Rebels at Massassi Station could run the Imperial blockade during the Evacuation of Yavin 4

properties.NAME: Arda system
properties.PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
properties.INTERESTING: the Steadfast (Jedi Master Eeth Koth's cruiser) attacked near this system during CW; Koth taken hostage by Grievous;

properties.NAME: Fara's Belt
properties.INTERESTING: site of Imperial communication station

properties.NAME: Ychthyton system
properties.INTERESTING: Ychthytonians: 4-armed, a few were known as bartenders

properties.PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

properties.NAME: R/M Facility Number Four
properties.NOTES: moved from Belderone? (placed there in Tarkin) to Mahrusha sector? (placed there in WEG Imperial Sourcebook)
properties.INTERESTING: largest Imperial Navy deepdock in operation during GCW; had 125 modular work bays, all of which were large enough to hold a strike cruiser; four could be combined to fit a VSD, 15 for an ISD, 18 for a Torpedo Sphere; modules were connected by Akinetic fields produced by Voorson power generators; new modules were constantly being added to existing structure

properties.NAME: Sooma
properties.INTERESTING: oxygen-filled atmosphere; R2 & C-3PO dispatched to Sooma as diplomatic couriers in decade prior to Yavin; attacked by Stenax in Stenax Massacres about 10 months after Endor

properties.NAME: Galidraan system

properties.NAME: Tobali system/Nabali system
properties.PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/

properties.NAME: Auratera
properties.INTERESTING: low-gravity world that contained a powerful vergence in the Force, centered at the structure known as Acablas; despite its placement on the busy Salin Corridor and location near many worlds of historic importance to the Jedi, Sith, and other Force users in the Outer Rim, the world was near-forgotten; during GCW, had only scattered settlements, some of which had reverted to primitive tech

properties.NAME: Columex
properties.PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
properties.INTERESTING: conquered by Xim; became capital of Commonality (confederacy of 5 sectors); within a few generations it became a major trade world, dominated by Humans known as Columexi; seceded during CW; Senator Simon Greyshade allowed the Empire to take some Commonality gambling profits in exchange for control of the Wheel (space station); ruled by Teradoc after Endor; razed by YV

properties.NAME: Cron Drift (Cron Cluster)
properties.INTERESTING: originally a small, beautiful, dynamic nebula; during Great Sith War, Aleema Keto used Sith device used to manipulate star matter to supernova nearby Cron Cluster (10 stars), destroying nearby planets and forming a giant asteroid field; later held a reputation as a hiding place for all sorts of illegal activity, pirating, looting, and smuggling; Rebel comm outpost here

properties.NAME: Shaltin system
properties.INTERESTING: shared name with Shaltin Tunnels hyperlane

properties.NAME: Indrexu Spiral/Ihala Spiral

properties.NAME: Galdria system
properties.INTERESTING: home to Galdrian mustang (type of horse that served as the favored mount of the Duinarbulon Star Lancers)

properties.NAME: Kismaano
properties.INTERESTING: rich windswept mining world, part of the Kingdom of Cron and Xim's Empire; member of Cronese Mandate by Imperial era; throughout its history it always stood apart from the rest of Cron, which had never trusted Kismaano's merchants; oldest settlements were built in side of canyons and rifts, and these had been tourist attractions for millennia (similar to those on Zonama Sekot)

properties.NAME: Panna system
properties.INTERESTING: populace consisted mostly of pirates, traders, prospectors; contained 7 planets (including 3 gas giants with extensive asteroid belts) and 35 moons; Xer VIII (pirate-lord) gathered a sizeable fleet here while he prepared to overthrow Ferece (Cronese king)

properties.NAME: Fial system
near Belderone/still considered far removed from major hyperlane such as Perlemian/coreward of Murkhana
properties.INTERESTING: located near Belderone, in Tion Cluster; coreward of Murkhana but still considered far removed from major hyperlanes such as the Perlemian; Empire had no presence here, but nearby Belderone was heavily fortified

properties.NAME: Pakuuni system
properties.PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
properties.INTERESTING: major haven for pirates, smugglers around the time of Hoth, causing galactic trade to be difficult or dangerous at best; Thrawn established outpost NL-1 in system before Endor

properties.NAME: Giryulan system

properties.INTERESTING: cluster of black holes, an obstacle Freia Kallea encountered when charting Hydian Way; many ships lost there, famously the Ashanda Ray, in which Kinnin Vo-Shay disappeared and reappeared 50 years later without having aged

properties.NAME: Fordon system
properties.INTERESTING: Jerresk (Quarren pirate) was last sighted here after carrying out a raid on a NR supply ship traveling to the Musson system

properties.NAME: Tythe
properties.INTERESTING: once as lush as Naboo until it became HQ of LiMerge Power, which stripped it of its resources to exploit its natural plasma reserves; later abandoned leaving only a desert wasteland; vegetation then found only in its red-water lakes; only tactical value was as a hyperspace jump point; garrisoned by Republic, then taken by CIS in 19 BBY

properties.NAME: Kaliida Shoals
properties.NOTES: Kaliida Shoals not listed on Ryndellia System page

properties.NAME: Kile
properties.INTERESTING: Rogue Squadron established a base, from which they launched a mission to rescue Han Solo from Boba Fett

properties.NAME: Zobbera system
properties.INTERESTING: home to zobberan hounds

properties.NAME: Tarnoonga
properties.KNOWN_ENVIRONMENTS: oceans, undersea mountain ranges, immense natural caves & grottos
properties.INTERESTING: home to giant sea monsters such as the Miridon, which made its nest in ruins of sunken freighter ships sitting atop undersea mountain ranges; Gir Kybo Ren-Cha (pirate) established a hideaway base in depths of one of these mountains (actually an island since it broke the surface of the waves), where he hid captured treasures from nearby worlds such as Tammuz-an; Luke contronted S'ybll here

properties.NAME: Koda Station
properties.PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game, Traveler's Guide to Batuu/
properties.INTERESTING: surrounding space mostly populated by planets with poor farming communities; many farmhands visited for excitement; smugglers also kept it busy despite its insignificance; fugitives Mammon Hoole, Tash Arranda, Zak Arranda used it as a temporary hideout 9 mo. after Yavin; station poorly maintained with trash lining hallways at that time; Nagai raiders attacked in 4 ABY

properties.INTERESTING: situated in space first explored 3000 - 1000 BBY, when it fell within Sith Brotherhood of Darkness territory; during CW, located in CIS space but Republic's Fifteenth Army was tasked with defending vicinity; situated within Imperial borders by 17 BBY; population 100 M - 500 M by 25 ABY

properties.NAME: Bajic system
properties.INTERESTING: flashpoint during GCW (at some point between 2 BBY & 4 ABY) with several battles fought here; Empire and Alliance victorious at various times

properties.NAME: Spice Terminus
properties.PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
properties.INTERESTING: major hub in the spice trade, near the end of the Llanic Spice Run and its intersection with the Five Veils Route

properties.NAME: Nixus
properties.INTERESTING: low-gravity; hosted Nixus Hub 218 (black market outpost visited by numerous individuals); site of deal between Vizago and Azmorigan, but Hondo imprisoned VIzago on his own ship and attempted to do the deal himself, leading to skirmish between the two and Ezra Bridger; later, the Spectres arrived to liberate two Lasat from the Empire and help them find Lira San (original Lasat homeworld)

properties.NAME: Atravis system
properties.PLACEMENT_LOGIC: Essential Atlas, TFA RPG Beginner Game/
properties.INTERESTING: scouted by Freia Kallea and Banu Hydia in 3694 BBY; surrounding area explored between 5000 and 3000 BBY; fell within CIS borders in 22 BBY; 18th Sector Army of Republic charged with engaging CIS forces here; civilians suffered extensive casualties during reign of Empire; population 1 - 10 B c. 25 ABY

properties.NAME: Tarabba system
properties.INTERESTING: center of communication, commerce in sector

properties.NAME: Orto Plutonia
properties.INTERESTING: home to Talz and narglatches; considered a protectorate of Pantora (its moon) until Pantorans discovered the Talz and them political self-determination after a brief conflict during CW (resolved by Anakin and Obi-Wan)

properties.NAME: Taroon system
properties.INTERESTING: in Imperial Space

properties.NAME: Lira San Nebula
properties.INTERESTING: treacherous nebula formed from an imploded star cluster; blocked the way to Lira San; Garazeb Orrelios used his bo staff in the ancient method to navigate a safe path between the gravitational anomalies in the nebula to reach his people's original homeworld
